Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesson 40 Waves\N\N海浪\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.02,0:00:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.56,0:00:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What false impression does an ocean wave convey to the observer?\N\N海浪给观者以什么假象?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Waves are the children of the struggle between ocean and atmosphere,\N\N海浪是大海和空气斗争的产物,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.17,0:00:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,signature: n.  签名，标记, infinity: n.  无穷\N\Nthe ongoing signatures of infinity.\N\N无限的一种不间断的标志.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.30,0:00:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,energize: v.  给与...能量\N\NRays from the sun excite and energize the atmosphere of the earth,\N\N太阳光刺激了地球的大气层,并给予它能量,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.07,0:00:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,rhythm: n.  节奏\N\Nawakening it to flow, to movement,to rhythm, to life.\N\N阳光使空气开始流动,产生节奏,获得生命.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.51,0:00:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind then speaks the message of the sun to the sea,\N\N然后,风把太阳的信息带给了大海,aa\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.73,0:00:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,transmit: v.  传送\N\Nand the sea transmits it on through waves --an ancient,exquisite powerful message.\N\N海洋用波浪的形式传递这个信息--一个源远流长、高雅而有力的信息.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.08,0:00:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena: n.  现象\N\NThese ocean waves are among the earth's most complicated natural phenomena.\N\N这些海浪属于地球上最复杂的自然现象.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.14,0:00:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,crest: n.  浪峰\N\NThe basic features include a crest (the highest point of the wave),\N\N它们的基本特征包括波峰(波浪的最高点),\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.96,0:00:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,trough: n.  波谷\N\Na trough (the lowest point),\N\N波谷(最低点),\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.71,0:01:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,crest: n.  浪峰, trough: n.  波谷\N\Na height (the vertical distance from the trough to the crest),\N\N浪高(从波谷到波峰的垂直距离),\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.37,0:01:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,crest: n.  浪峰\N\Na wave length(the horizontal distance between two wave crests),\N\N波长(两个波峰间的水平距离),\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.27,0:01:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,crest: n.  浪峰\N\Nand a period(which is the time it takes a wave crest to travel one wave length).\N\N和周期(浪峰走过一个波长所需的时间).\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.18,0:01:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Although an ocean wave give the impression of a wall of water moving in your direction,\N\N虽然,海浪给人的印象是一堵由水组成的墙向你压过来,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.37,0:01:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality: n.  现实\N\Nin actuality waves move through the water leaving the water about where it was.\N\N而实际上,浪从水中移过,而水则留在原处.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.75,0:01:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If the water was moving with the wave,\N\N如果水和浪一起移动的话,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.39,0:01:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the ocean and everything on it,\N\N那么大海和海里的东西,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.78,0:01:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would be racing in to the shore with obviously catastrophic results.\N\N就会向岸边疾涌而来,带来明显的灾难性后果.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.72,0:01:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,An ocean wave passing through deep water,\N\N穿过深水的海浪,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.38,0:01:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,particle: n.  微粒\N\Ncauses a particle on the surface to move in a roughly circular orbit,\N\N使水面上的一个微粒按照一种近乎圆形的轨道移动,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.72,0:01:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,particle: n.  微粒\N\Ndrawing the particle first towards the advancing wave,\N\N先把微粒拉向前移的海浪,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.38,0:01:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,then up into the wave, then forward with it and then--\N\N然后推上波浪,随着波浪移动,然后--\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:02:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,particle: n.  微粒\N\Nas the wave leaves the particles behind-- back to its starting point again.\N\N当波浪把微粒留在身后时--又回到出发点.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.55,0:02:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,maturity: n.  成熟\N\NFrom both maturity to death,\N\N从成熟到消亡,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.70,0:02:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a wave is subject to the same laws as any other 'living' thing.\N\N波浪和其他任何"活动中"的东西一样,都受制于共同的法则.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,For a time it assumes a miraculous individuality that, in the end,\N\N一度它获得非凡的个性,但最终,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.77,0:02:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is reabsorbed into the great ocean of life.\N\N又被重新融进生命的大洋.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.19,0:02:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The undulating waves of the open sea are generated by three natural causes:\N\N公海上起伏的波浪是由3个自然因素构成的:\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.64,0:02:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,tremor: n.  震颤\N\Nwind,earth movements or tremors,and the gravitational pull of the moon and the sun.\N\N风、地球的运动或震颤和月亮、太阳的引力.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.62,0:02:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Once waves have been generated,gravity is the force that drives them in a continual attempt,to restore the ocean surface to a flat plain.\N\N一旦波浪形成,地球引力是持续不断企图,使海面复原为平面的力量.\N\N